definitions.definition: the state or fact of being strange.
examples: oddity, eccentricity, peculiarity, curiousness, bizarreness, weirdness, queerness, unusualness, abnormality, unaccountability, inexplicability, incongruousness, outlandishness, singularity there was a strangeness about Wally that I couldn't quite explain

definitions.definition: one of six flavors of quark.
